25 Neither shall ye offer the gifts of your God of all these things by the hand of a stranger, because there is <RF><i>Gr.</i> corruptions.<Rf>corruption in them, a blemish in them: these shall not be accepted for you.
26 And the Lord spoke to Moses, saying,
27 As for a calf, or a sheep, or a goat, whenever it is born, then shall it be seven days under its mother; and on the eighth day and after they shall be accepted for sacrifices, a burnt-offering to the Lord.
28 And a <RF><i>Gr.</i> calf.<Rf>bullock and a <RF><i>Gr.</i> sheep.<Rf>ewe, it and its young, thou shalt not kill in one day.<CM>
29 And if thou shouldest offer a sacrifice, a vow of rejoicing to the Lord, ye shall offer it so as to be accepted for you.
