7 And if from sixty year <FI>old<Fi> and upward, if it be a male, his valuation shall be fifteen didrachms of silver, and if a female, ten didrachms.
8 And if the man be too poor for the valuation, he shall stand before the priest; and the priest shall value him: according to what the man who has vowed can afford, the priest shall value him.<CM>
