the fourteenth day of the twelfth month Adar, of the present year; that the people aforetime and now ill-disposed <FI>to us<Fi> having been violently consigned to death in one day, may hereafter secure to us continually a well constituted and quiet <FI>state of affairs.<Fi> ]<CM>
