1 <T>For the end. Destroy not: by David, for a memorial, when he fled from the presence of Saul to the cave.<t><CM>Have mercy, upon me, O God, have mercy upon me: for my soul has trusted in thee: and in the shadow of thy wings will I hope, until the iniquity have passed away.
