1 <T>For the end, for them that shall yet be changed; for an inscription by David for instruction, when he <FI>had<Fi> burned Mesopotamia of Syria, and Syria Sobal, and Joab <FI>had<Fi> returned and smitten <FI>in<Fi> the valley of salt twelve thousand.<t><CM>O God, thou hast rejected and destroyed us; thou hast been angry, yet hast pitied us.
