5 Come and behold the works of God; <FI>he is<Fi> terrible in <FI>his<Fi> counsels beyond the children of men.
6 Who turns the sea into dry land; they shall go through the river on foot; there shall we rejoice in him,
7 who by his power <RF><i>Or</i>, has dominion for ever.<Rf>is Lord over the age, his eyes look upon the nations; let not them that provoke <FI>him<Fi> be exalted in themselves. Pause.<CM>
